<HEAD>Italian Townspeople Express Solidarity with Hostage</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Hostages, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRESAGRANDINARIA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Citizens of the town where Joseph
Cicippio's family is from have called on the Italian government to
help free him and other Western hostages held in Lebanon.
   Speaking on Italian TV Tuesday, Mayor Giovanni Di Stefano
expressed the townspeople's solidarity with Cicippio.
   He said that he and other people in the town of 1,400 located
