<FIRST>r w AM-Bush-PepperSeat     08-08 0202</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bush-Pepper Seat,190</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bush to Campaign in Florida en Route to Maine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush will make a detour to Miami on
his way to Maine next week to campaign for the Republican seeking
the late Claude Pepper's congressional seat, the White House said
Tuesday.
   Bush will appear in Miami next Wednesday at a rally for Ileana
Ros-Lehtinen, a Cuban-American and former state senator vying for
the seat left vacant when the 88-year-old Democratic dean of
Congress died in May.
   Bush's son Jeb, former Dade County Republican chairman and
Florida secretary of commerce, is managing her campaign.
   The Democrats will choose their nominee in a runoff next
Tuesday, and the special election will be Aug. 29.
   Bush is planning to spend Aug. 16-Sept. 5 at his oceanfront home
in Kennebunkport, Maine.
   White House spokesman Marlin Fitzwater joked about the
2,500-mile detour on the journey northward, ``So we're going to
Florida on the way to Maine. It's a fairly common route.''
   He said Bush has no plans yet to campaign in Texas or California
where other elections are coming up to fill seats vacated by two
other prominent Democrats who resigned, former Speaker Jim Wright
and majority whip Tony Coelho.
</TEXT>
