<HEAD>Police Blame Car's Fumes for Three Deaths</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An automobile left running in the basement
garage of an apartment house has been blamed for the deaths of
three elderly people, police said Tuesday.
   The body of Earle Zahm, 87, was found Monday after police were
called to investigate an odor coming from his first-floor apartment.
   Later in the day, the body of 79-year-old Mary Rose Liermann was
