<HEAD>The President Needed a Haircut</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto WX23</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush delivered a speech at the
National Urban League conference on Tuesday with his usually neatly
combed-back hair flopping on his forehead. A change of hair style?
Nope: Bush just needed a haircut, the White House said.
   Bush made the appearance shortly after he jogged for 30 minutes,
and his hair was not quite dry as he spoke to the civil rights
group.
   The final event on Bush's calendar, in fact, was a haircut.
   ``He isn't changing his hair style. Wait until you see him
tomorrow after his haircut before drawing any conclusions,'' said
deputy press secretary Stephen Hart.
</TEXT>
