<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--DEADeath     08-08 0145</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--DEA Death,0150</SECOND>
<HEAD>Autopsy: Drug Agent Died Of Heroine Overdose</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A special agent for the Drug Enforcement
Administration died of an overdose of heroine, according to autopsy
results announced Tuesday.
   Gary St. Hilaire's death occurred Aug. 1 at his home in Babylon
on Long Island, said DEA special agent and spokesman Robert Strang.
   St. Hilaire, 33, married and the father of two children, had
been assigned to drug enforcement at Kennedy International Airport
for the last three years after working for three years in other
assignments throughout the city, Strang said.
   The spokesman said he had minimal information about the death.
   ``We're determining the circumstances surrounding his death,''
he said. ``There is an investigation. It would be premature to
speculate as to what happened.''
   There are more than 500 DEA agents and investigators assigned to
the New York field division.
