<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The FBI believes the body of American hostage
William R. Higgins was shown in a videotape released by terrorists
but says there can be no positive identification without physical
evidence.
   The FBI offered no information about the time or cause of the
Marine lieutenant colonel's death when it said Monday that the
videotaped body hanging by a rope was probably that of Higgins.
   FBI forensic experts concluded ``within a reasonable degree of
medical certainty that the person depicted in the videotape is
dead,'' the bureau said.
   ``Although a positive identification could not be made, numerous
observable characteristics were noted indicating that the person
depicted in the videotape is Lt. Col. Higgins,'' the FBI said.
