<TEXT>
   President Bush signed into law Monday a $70
billion increase in the federal debt limit, increasing the
borrowing ceiling to $2.87 trillion from $2.80 trillion.
   The new debt limit will expire on Oct. 31, 1989. The debt
ceiling is increased once or twice a year as the government amasses
annual budget deficits.
