   The stock market inched higher this morning
toward new post-crash highs.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, which surged Monday to
within 30 points of its record close reached nearly two years ago,
advanced 1.14 by 10 a.m. EDT to 2,696.13.
   Among broader market indicators, the New York Stock Exchange
Composite index of all listed issues rose 0.02 to 194.21. On the
American Stock Exchange, the market value index rose 0.10 to 379.28.
