waning anxiety over the possibility of recession. Many brokers said
that combination compelled many investors to shift more money into
stocks.
   Nonetheless, others question how long the rally will last. Much
of the strength in the market lately has been derived from takeover
speculation and computer-assisted buying strategies that aren't
based on stocks as a long-term investment.
   On Monday the Dow Jones industrial average jumped 41.54 points
to 2,694.99, which is 27.43 points shy of the record closing high
of 2,722.42 reached on Aug. 25, 1987.
   Advancing issues outnumbered declines by more than 2 to 1 on the
NYSE, with 1,056 up, 451 down and 472 unchanged.
   Big Board volume totaled 197.58 million shares, against 169.75
million in the previous session.
