46{ Monday. The company disclosed it received a buyout offer from
investor Marvin Davis. AMR was up 1| to 73[ and Delta rose 1\ to
75} and Pan Am was up [ at 4[ in heavy trading.
   The Monday rally was incited by takeover-related buying and
waning anxiety over the possibility of recession. Many brokers said
that combination compelled many investors to shift more money into
stocks.
   Nonetheless, others question how long the rally will last. Much
of the strength in the market lately has been derived from takeover
speculation and computer-assisted buying strategies that aren't
based on stocks as a long-term nvestment.
   On Monday, the Dow industrial average jumped 41.54 points to
2,694.99, is 27.43 points shy of the record closing high of
2,722.42 reached on Aug. 25, 1987.
