<FIRST>r f AM-Earns-NewmontMining     08-08 0180</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Earns-Newmont Mining,0186</SECOND>
<HEAD>Newmont Mining Reports Reduced Second-Quarter Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Newmont Mining Corp. on Tuesday reported reduced
second-quarter earnings of $7.2 million, or 11 cents per share,
down from $19.4 million during the same period in 1988.
   The Denver-based firm, which holds a 90 percent interest in
Newmont Gold Co. and 75 percent interest in Newmont Australia Ltd.,
reported that its quarter earnings came on sales of $174.4 million.
   During the comparable three-month period ending on June 30,
1988, when Newmont's per-share earnings were 29 cents, the company
reported $113 million in sales.
   Newmont said the most recent quarter earnings suffered from net
after-tax charges of $5 million for costs associated with a plan to
recapitalize Peabody Holding Co. Inc., and $3.6 million to revise a
gain recorded in 1988 on a discontinued operation.
   During the first six months of 1989, the company reported net
income of $16.6 million, or 25 cents per share, compared with
$133.8 million, or $1.99 per share, during the first two quarters
of 1988. Revenue rose to $306.7 million from $205.4 million.
